        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 5:29PM CDT until June 8 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles southeast of
Gordon, or 17 miles north of Stephenville, moving southeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Morgan Mill around 540 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include
Hannibal, Patillo, Thurber, and Mingus.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection stay inside a sturdy structure and keep away from
windows.</instruction>
